	<h3 class="left-20p">DISCIPLESHIP OBJECTIVES for 2014:</h3><br/>
		<p class="bottom-10">1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	Finish the official C8 Curriculum topics by July and the complete lessons by November</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">2.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish and monitor an Old Testament and New Testament reading Programs for every church member</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">3.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Require all official members to join a formal discipleship program, especially the Care Flocks that will study together the Curriculum of Eight (8)</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">4.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mobilize all the professional teachers among the members to help in making the official lesson plans for the said curriculum</p>
		<p class="bottom-10">5.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Centralize all Sunday School classes and integrate the weekly house prayer meetings in line with the C8 Campaign goals starting July </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">6.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hold at least once a year official Leaders Training and Seminar starting June and require every leader and workers to attend it. </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">7.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish an official Follow Up team per age level to minister to new Christians and those who are in a state of “lukewarmness and backsliding “ </p>
		<p class="bottom-10">8.	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make an official C8 Curriculum Library starting September </p>

		
